This paper focuses on the development of a quadrupedal microrobot and its locomotion capabilities, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of proprioceptive sensing and control is a key aspect of the work, which suggests the sub-category of systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also mentions the use of piezoelectric actuation, which falls under the sub-category of electromagnetics (cs.EM). The development of the microrobot also involves advances in manufacturing, which could be categorized under mechanical engineering (cs.ME). Finally, the paper mentions the use of bioinspired parametric leg trajectories, which could involve computer vision techniques for analyzing biological locomotion, placing the paper under the sub-category of computer vision (cs.CV).
